<HEADLINE>
<P>
FRANCES GUENETTE; TV EXECUTIVE, PRODUCTION COMPANY CO-FOUNDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Frances Guenette, 59, co-founder with her husband of Robert Guenette 
Productions. A native of Vienna, Mrs. Guenette immigrated to New York as a 
child.After studying at the University of Michigan, she began working for CBS' 
"Studio One." She eventually became an associate producer and created 
"Conquest," "Odyssey," "Appointment With Destiny" and "Eye on the World." In 
1975, she became a principal in Guenette-Asselin Productions in Los Angeles and 
later helped establish Robert Guenette Productions, in which she served as vice 
president. The company's work included "Children of the Night" for CBS, "Extra 
Dimension" for Group W and "Counterattack: Crime in America" for ABC. Since 
1990, Mrs. Guenette had served as president of the Los Angeles Opera Assn. 
support group. On Monday in Beverly Hills of ovarian cancer. 
</P>
