<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY : VENTURA; CITY HELPING TO SPONSOR ART WALK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city of Ventura is sponsoring an art walk today in conjunction with area 
coffeehouses and art galleries to promote the downtown area, which city leaders 
are trying to revitalize. 
</P>
<P>
 Twenty-five galleries and seven coffeehouses in downtown are participating in 
the free, one-day event, scheduled from 5 to 9:30 p.m. Some coffeehouses plan 
to offer free samples during the "Java Jump," as the event is called. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a self-led tour," said Sonia Tower, the city's cultural affairs 
coordinator. "You pick up a map at any of the galleries." 
</P>
<P>
 For those who don't feel like walking, two courtesy shuttle vans will operate 
among art galleries, Tower said. 
</P>
<P>
 At 9 p.m., drawings for prizes will be held at City Hall's first-floor atrium, 
and some refreshments and entertainment will be provided. 
</P>
<P>
 Tower said only art galleries traditionally had participated in the walk that 
is held periodically, but this year city officials decided to add coffeehouses 
because several had recently opened downtown. 
</P>
<P>
 "There's a natural link between the coffeehouses and the galleries, because 
many of the coffeehouses have art exhibits up on an ongoing basis," Tower said. 
PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
