WEST VENTURA COUNTY : OXNARD; POLICE INVESTIGATE GUNFIGHT THAT HURT 2 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Oxnard police are investigating an early morning gunfight outside a fast-food 
restaurant that left two men injured, one of them critically, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The shooting occurred about 3 a.m. Thursday at Del Taco in the 500 block of 
South Ventura Road, but both victims were found elsewhere, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Travon Lanell Netherly, 25, of Los Angeles was discovered bleeding in his car 
after his companion, 23-year-old Darrin Johnson of Los Angeles, hailed 
firefighters. 
</P>
<P>
 Netherly, who was shot in the chest, was listed in serious but stable 
condition Friday at St. John's Regional Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
 The second victim, Eric Pantoja, 23, of Oxnard, was found bleeding at a 
relative's apartment near the restaurant. He was listed in fair condition at 
St. John's with a gunshot wound to the abdomen, but police said his wound was 
not life-threatening. 
</P>
<P>
 Sgt. Charles Dunham said police believe Pantoja was meeting with Johnson and 
Netherly when the men had a disagreement and shots were fired. Police found a 
.380-caliber handgun registered to Netherly in Netherly's car. 
</P>
<P>
 No arrests have been made, and Dunham said none of the three people involved 
is cooperating with investigators. JULIE FIELDS 
