<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEW PROJECTS AT DISNEYLAND, KNOTT'S 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As Six Flags Magic Mountain and Universal Studios Hollywood battle it out this 
spring with their new attractions, Disneyland and Knott's Berry Farm also have 
new projects: 
</P>
<P>
 Knott's Berry Farm: On Memorial Day weekend, the Buena Park attraction plans 
to open Thunder Falls. The area will be highlighted by Mystery Lodge, a 
special-effects attraction that will tell a story based on the traditions of 
the Native American peoples of the Northwest Pacific Coast.Thunder Falls, which 
represents Knott's Berry Farm's largest expansion since 1988, will also include 
a plaza with street entertainment and a museum store that will sell authentic 
Native American crafts. 
</P>
<P>
 Disneyland: The Anaheim park added Roger Rabbit's Car Toon Spin to the 
Mickey's Toontown area in January. A high-tech parade based on Disney's 
upcoming animated feature, "The Lion King," is expected to begin in July, and 
the theme park will introduce a thrill ride based on the Indiana Jones films 
early next year. 
</P>
