<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND TV; FOUR WOMEN DISCUSS THEIR 'SUCCESS STORIES' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By N.F. MENDOZA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Four Los Angeles businesswomen, who have coped with civil unrest and 
earthquakes, discuss their lives and careers on "Success Stories," today at 6 
p.m. on KCET Channel 28. 
</P>
<P>
 On Sunday at 8 p.m. on KCET, PBS' "Nature" focuses on the Monterey Bay 
Aquarium where, for the past nine years, researchers have taught survival 
skills to Pacific sea otter orphans who otherwise face death. 
</P>
<P>
 The Whitewater affair and health-care reform will continue to be prime topics 
on the public service programs. N.F. MENDOZA 
</P>
