<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; SCHULLERS TO MARK 40 YEARS OF MINISTRY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WILLSON CUMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Robert and Arvella Schuller will mark their 40th year of ministry at the 
Crystal Cathedral on Sunday by re-creating their original services at a 
drive-in movie theater. 
</P>
<P>
 The Schullers plan to appear in a replica of the 1953 Chevrolet they drove to 
their first services at the movie theater.  
</P>
<P>
 Arvella Schuller said she will play the organ she used in the 1950s. Actor 
Charlton Heston will join the celebration to talk about the first Schuller 
service. 
</P>
<P>
 Services will be held Sunday at 8:30, 9:30 and 11 a.m. at the Crystal 
Cathedral, 12141 Lewis St.  
</P>
<P>
 A special celebration is planned at 10:30 a.m. in the church plaza. WILLSON 
CUMMER 
</P>
