<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN HELD AFTER DEATH OF BABY BOY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 22-month-old boy died Friday at Hoag Hospital, where he had been admitted 
with injuries for the second time in a weeks. His mother's boyfriend was 
arrested, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Laudenback, 32, of Newport Beach was booked on suspicion of corporal 
punishment or injury to a child, according to Sgt. Andy Gonis, and held on 
$10,000 bail. More serious charges may be filed following an autopsy, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The child, Tyler Jaeger, had been admitted to Hoag Hospital March 18 with a 
fractured skull, according to Gonis. 
</P>
<P>
 Hospital officials were told at the time that the infant's head injury was 
caused by an accidental fall, Gonis said, and because the injuries were 
consistent with such an injury, the baby was released two days later to the 
custody of his mother, Karey Jaeger. 
</P>
<P>
 The baby was returned to the Hoag emergency room at 10.45 a.m. Friday by 
Laudenback, but could not be revived and was pronounced dead. 
</P>
<P>
 Because of bruising on the child, police were called and both Laudenback and 
Jaeger, who live together, were questioned. 
</P>
<P>
 Karey Jaeger was released without charge, Gonis said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
