<P>
POLICE ARREST MAN IN 20 AREA BURGLARIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After two days of surveillance, Orange County sheriff's undercover deputies 
arrested an armed, 23-year-old salesman Thursday suspected of 20 area 
burglaries. 
</P>
<P>
 Jon Duncan Gaw was arrested on suspicion of residential burglary as he crawled 
out of an unoccupied house, according to deputies contracted to patrol Lake 
Forest.Gaw is being held in the Orange County Jail on $250,000 bail, Lt. Dan 
Martini said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 On Thursday, police said Gaw was observed at a house on Via Del Rio, leaving 
after someone answered the door. Gaw then went to a house on Camino Villa and, 
when there was no answer, climbed through a window on the side of the house, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Apparently, Gaw spotted the undercover deputies outside the house and left the 
residence. As Gaw approached his car, he was taken into custody, and police 
found he had a loaded semiautomatic pistol. 
</P>
