<HEADLINE>
<P>
FULLERTON, SADDLEBACK TOURNAMENTS BEGIN SUNDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fullerton and Saddleback colleges play host to softball tournaments starting 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Fullerton tournament will be at Tamarack Park and Fullerton College. 
</P>
<P>
 The first-round games at Fullerton are: Cerritos vs. Moorpark, 10:30 a.m.; 
Fullerton vs. Chabot, 12:30 p.m., and Pasadena vs. Bakersfield, 2:30 p.m. Mt. 
San Antonio takes on Sierra at 9:30 a.m. at Tamarack Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago, Long Beach and Chaffey have first-round byes. 
</P>
<P>
 The tournament continues with two more rounds Sunday and the title game is 
Monday at 3 p.m. at Fullerton College. 
</P>
<P>
 In the first round of the Saddleback tournament: Mesa (Ariz.) goes against 
Imperial Valley and San Diego City takes on defending champion Riverside at 10 
a.m. Citrus plays San Jose and East Los Angeles and Saddleback meet at noon. 
</P>
<P>
 Cosumnes River, Grossmont, El Camino and Dixie (Utah) have first-round byes. 
The tournament continues Monday and the title game is Tuesday at 6 p.m. 
</P>
