<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; TITANS RALLY IN 10TH INNING TO GET PAST SAN JOSE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton needed extra innings for the second consecutive game to 
win. This time the Titans scored four runs in the 10th inning and went on to 
beat San Jose State, 7-3, in the Big West Conference opener for both teams 
Friday at San Jose. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton (22-6) was coming off a 13-inning, 5-4 victory over Wichita State on 
Wednesday. The Titans scored a run in the ninth to take a 3-2 lead but San Jose 
came back to tie it on a Tim Gavello's RBI single. 
</P>
<P>
 Bret Hemphill put Fullerton up, 5-4, with a sacrifice fly that scored Dante 
Powell in the 10th. Adam Millan followed with a two-run double. 
</P>
<P>
 Ted Silva, who allowed the run in the ninth, pitched a scoreless 10th for the 
victory. Silva, a sophomore right-hander, is 3-1. Chad Rolish allowed two runs 
in seven innings but got no decision. 
</P>
<P>
 The teams meet today and Sunday at 1 p.m. San Jose State, which had a 
seven-game winning streak stopped, is 17-11. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Redlands softball tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Chapman wins two of three -- Susan Caton pitched pitched a two-hitter and 
struck out three as Chapman beat Menlo, 14-1, in a game called after three 
innings because of a time limit. Bernie Fancuberta had two hits on the day 
including a double, two RBIs and two runs scored and Lisa Simpson scored three 
runs, and hit a double and two singles. Chapman also beat Redlands, 3-0, and 
lost to Gustavus-Adolphus, 2-0. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Spring Fling tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California College 3, Lovile (Ala.) 0 -- Shannon Osyala pitched her 
fifth shutout of the season, a two-hitter with four strikeouts, for for SCC 
(23-5, 6-1). Amy Lewis scored two runs and Angie Vega had a RBI single in sixth 
for SCC. Shannon Osyala had fifth shut out, with four strikeouts. 
</P>
<P>
 SCC faces West Florida one semifinals today. In earlier pool play, West 
Florida handed SCC its only lost of the tournament, 1-0. 
</P>
