UCI TRACK AND FIELD HOME OPENER SET FOR TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The UC Irvine men's and women's track and field teams will play host to their 
1994 home opener today against Cal State Fullerton, Weber State, Cal State Los 
Angeles and Cal Poly Pomona. 
</P>
<P>
 Field events begin with the hammer throw at 11:30 a.m. The women's 5,000 
meters begins the running events at 12:10 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Laura Monson, Irvine's freshman distance runner, will run the 1,500 while 
attempting to win an event in a meet for the fifth consecutive time.All her 
victories, however, have come at 3,000 or 5,000; she has twice run second in 
the 1,500. 
</P>
<P>
 Senior Traci Goodrich, a 1992 All-American in the 10,000 meters and Big West 
runner-up in cross-country last fall, is expected to make her season debut in 
the 3,000 today after undergoing arthroscopic surgery on her left knee in 
January. 
</P>
