<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALL-STAR WRESTLING; THIS MATCH IS A 'FUN THING' FOR 30 SENIORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIM Q. BERKSHIRE, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three practice sessions didn't put them in peak postseason form, but for the 
30 seniors who gathered for the Orange County All-Star Wrestling match Friday 
night at University High, it didn't matter. 
</P>
<P>
 This night, to honor their high school wrestling accomplishments, was more 
about fun. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's good for the kids, it's a compliment for the seniors, it's just a fun 
thing," said Santa Ana Coach Scott Glabb, who coached the winning Red team. 
</P>
<P>
 Led by State champion Darryl Christian of Canyon and a strong supporting cast, 
the Red team took a 28-22 decision over the Blue team, coached by Steve Stewart 
of University. 
</P>
<P>
 Had it not been for Stewart's generosity, the Red team would have struggled to 
prevail. 
</P>
<P>
 Red team member Eric Escobedo of Huntington Beach (171 pounds) was a no-show 
and Woodbridge's Jesse Liu (189) was out with an injured shoulder. Rather than 
forfeiting two matches, Stewart allowed the Blue team's Scott Rojo (189) to 
switch teams and drop a weight class -- to 171 -- to wrestle Capistrano 
Valley's Terry Tuzzolino. 
</P>
<P>
 Mission Viejo's Rojo, the South Coast League and Division I Southern Section 
champion took a 4-1 lead in the second period and held on to win, 4-3. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's nice to finish the season with a win," said Rojo, who was just as 
ecstatic to end the season with a victory against Tuzzolino. "I was pretty 
nervous. It's intimidating to go against a guy who's second in the state." 
</P>
<P>
 Rojo had practiced with Tuzzolino, the Division I section and Masters champion 
and runner-up in the State meet, this week and thought they were evenly 
matched. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was fun. There were a lot of good wrestlers here. It was an honor to be 
here," Rojo said. 
</P>
<P>
 Behind Magnolia's Dan Jurado (103) and Santa Ana's Roger Santiago (112), the 
Red team took a 6-0 lead. The Blue team countered with victories by Savanna's 
Randy Bowers (119), Orange's Jason Bress (125), Buena Park's Vince Virgen 
(130), El Dorado's Tommy Noel (130) and Calvary Chapel's Mauricio Mora (135) -- 
who defeated State champion Juan Alvarez of El Modena -- for a 16-6 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 El Modena's David Wells (140) defeated State runner-up Alfred Frausto of 
Edison for the Red team, and Christian (140), Chris Jaime of El Modena (145), 
San Clemente's John Witting (152) and Newport Harbor's Chris Edwards (160) won 
for the 22-16 Red team lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Victories by Rojo and Marc Albert of Los Alamitos (171) secured the Red team 
victory, although Buena Park's Wali Sibrie had the only pin of the match to 
pull the Blue team to the 28-22 final. 
</P>
</TEXT>
