<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; VILLA PARK FINALLY BEATS FOOTHILL IN SWIMMING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Villa Park boys' and girls' swimming teams beat Foothill for the first 
time in 20 years the teams have met. The Villa park boys won, 98-72, and the 
girls won, 100-76. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Pharris won the 200 individual medley (2:09.16), the 100 butterfly 
(57.63) and swam the final leg on the winning 200 medley relay and 200 
freestyle relay for Villa Park (4-0, 2-0). Teammate Kevin Bobzien won the 50 
(21.46) and 100 (48.93) freestyle and also competed on the winning relays. 
Andrew Smallman won the 200 freestyle (1:54) and 500 freestyle (5:09.37). 
Foothill is 2-3, 1-1. 
</P>
<P>
 In Century League girls' swimming: 
</P>
<P>
 Villa Park 100, Foothill 70 -- Tea Lindberg won the 200 individual medley 
(2:22.56) and the 100 breaststroke (1:10.72) for Villa Park (4-0, 2-0). Jessica 
Klugman finished first in the 200 freestyle (2:07.77), the 100 freestyle 
(57.95). Foothill is 1-4, 1-1. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague girls' swimming: 
</P>
<P>
 Costa Mesa 102, Westminster 47 -- Sophomore Katie Grogan won the 200 
individual medley (2:36.75) and 500 freestyle (6:01.53) and freshman Colleen 
Lund placed first in the 100 freestyle (1:03.59) and 100 backstroke (1:13.82). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague boys' swimming: 
</P>
<P>
 Costa Mesa 128, Westminster 6 -- James Comfort swam a Southern Section 
qualifying time of 59.08 in the 100 backstroke to lead Costa Mesa (3-1, 1-0). 
Comfort also won the 200 individual medley (2:09.22). Bernard Perone won the 
200 freestyle (1:59.15) and 500 freestyle (5:20.66) for the Mustangs. 
</P>
<P>
 In Olympic League softball: 
</P>
<P>
 Heritage Christian 20, Claremont 3 (5, mercy) -- Sheri Larson was four for 
five with five RBIs for Heritage Christian (4-2, 3-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In Sunset League softball: 
</P>
<P>
 Marina 6, Westminster 2 -- Marcy Crouch (5-0) pitched a three-hitter and 
Lynette Velazquez had two hits, including a double and two RBIs for Marina 
(7-0, 2-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague softball: 
</P>
<P>
 Loara 2, Villa Park 0 -- Chrissy Hartman had two hits, an RBI, and pitched a 
three-hitter to lead Loara (7-4). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague boys' tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei 15, Costa Mesa 6 -- Paul Kerwin swept at No. 1 singles, 6-0, 6-0, 
6-0 and Miles Simon won, 6-0, 6-1, 6-2, at No. 2 singles for visiting Mater Dei 
(2-2). 
</P>
