<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANGELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB NIGHTENGALE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Angels did make one trade Friday, sending minor-league reliever Bob Gamez 
to the San Francisco Giants for outfielder Steve Hosey. Hosey, who hit .292 
with 16 homers and 85 RBIs at triple-A Phoenix, is expected to open the season 
as the starting right fielder in triple-A Vancouver."He's in Bo's shadow," 
Rodgers said, "but our feeling was that we needed a right-handed hitter in 
triple-A in case something happens to Bo. Bo will probably be here one year at 
the most, anyway. If (Jackson) plays bad, we'll get rid of him; and if he plays 
good, he'll get rid of us." . . . The Angels game against the Oakland Athletics 
was rained out, so what do they do for entertainment? DH Chili Davis gave left 
fielder Eduardo Perez a haircut. . . . Mark Leiter, who has had a mild strain 
of his lower back, was pushed back to Sunday. . . . Starter Joe Magrane, who 
isn't expected to be ready until the end of April, was placed on the 15-day 
disabled list. BOB NIGHTENGALE 
</P>
