<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; CYPRESS' LOPEZ PITCHES SHUTOUT TO BEAT SADDLEBACK IN 
SOFTBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jenny Lopez pitched a two-hitter as Cypress beat Saddleback, 4-0, in an Orange 
Empire Conference softball game Friday at Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
 Lopez (5-4) had six strikeouts and five walks for host Cypress (23-10, 
4-5).Alison Murphy had three hits, including a double, scored a run and drove 
in another. 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback is 15-9, 4-5. 
</P>
<P>
 In Orange Empire Conference women's swimming: 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago 129, Cypress 54 -- Freshman Michelle Morris was a triple 
winner for Rancho Santiago. Morris, who is undefeated in dual meets, won the 
100 breaststroke (1:11.3), the 50 butterfly (28.9) and 200 individual medley 
(2:16.8). Teammate Karen Sill won the 50 freestyle (26.9), 100 freestyle (59.1) 
and 500 freestyle (6:37.2). 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast 131, San Diego Mesa 87 -- Orange Coast won every individual and 
relay race in winning its 91st consecutive dual meet. 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 155, Palomar 142 -- Saddleback clinched the meet with a victory in 
the 200 freestyle relay, the last event of the meet. Kristine Palle won the 100 
freestyle (1:00.16), the 200 freestyle (2:05.44) and the 500 freestyle 
(5:49.36) and also was the anchor leg of the 200 freestyle relay team. 
</P>
<P>
 In women's South Coast Conference swimming: 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West 99, El Camino 30 -- Kate Kilgallen, June Mitrais, Jennifer Ullrich 
and Belinda Kernkamp each won two races for Golden West (3-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In Orange Empire Conference men's swimming: 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago 103, Cypress 67 -- Chad Gniffke won the 200 individual medley 
(2:24.3) and 200 breaststroke (2:42) for visiting Rancho Santiago. May Miyahara 
won the 200 freestyle (1:56.0) and 500 freestyle (5:21.3) for Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
 In men's South Coast Conference swimming: 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West 71, El Camino 32 -- Matt Braun won the 100 freestyle in 50.82 and 
the 50 freestyle in 22.92 to lead Golden West (3-0). 
</P>
