<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; JONES' HOMER GIVES CSUN 3-0 SOFTBALL WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Shannon Jones hit a three-run home run in the seventh inning and Amy 
Windmiller pitched a one-hitter as Cal State Northridge defeated Oregon, 3-0, 
to complete pool play Friday in the Cal State Fullerton softball tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Jones drove in Tamara Ivie and Scia Maumausolo with her fourth home run of the 
season. 
</P>
<P>
 Windmiller (11-1) walked one and struck out 10. In her last seven starts -- 
all victories -- she has given up five hits and one run in 45 innings. During 
that span, she has four no-hitters, including two perfect games. 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge (21-3) was to start single-elimination bracket play against Georgia 
State on Friday night, but the game was postponed until noon today because of 
rain. BASEBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Valley 6, Canyons 4 -- Ozzie Areu hit a two-run homer in the first inning and 
added a double in the third as the host Monarchs (8-12-1, 6-5 in conference 
play) won a Western State Conference game. 
</P>
<P>
 David Stevenson extended his hitting streak to 12 games with two doubles. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyons stranded 13 runners, leaving the bases loaded in the seventh and two 
runners on in the eighth as Juan Dorado picked up his first save of the season. 
</P>
<P>
 Pierce 10, Santa Monica 2 -- Rusty Howard replaced injured Brandon Nickens in 
the fourth inning and led the Brahmas to a WSC victory at Marine Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Nickens left after stiffness developed in his elbow. Howard pitched four 
innings, giving up two hits and striking out three. 
</P>
<P>
 Caesar Martinez had two hits, scored three runs and stole four bases for 
Pierce. 
</P>
</TEXT>
